  "plainText": "Don't Starve\nTogether\nUnagi\nFood Info\n18.75\n20\n5\nMeat\nObject Info\n10 days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x2\n10 sec\n20\nMiscellaneous\n\"unagi\"\n“I hope this doesn't make me feel eel!”\n–Wilson\n“You can make it fancy but it's still an eel.”\n–Willow\n“Food makes me mighty!”\n–Wolfgang\n“It looks more appetizing this way.”\n–Wendy\n“A FANCIER FUEL PACK.”\n–WX-78\n“A common way to prepare eel.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“It'll fill ya up.”\n–Woodie\n“It will have to do.”\n–Maxwell\n“I do hope this doesn't cause stomach upset.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Nö need för fööd tö be sö fancy.”\n–Wigfrid\n“It was easy to make with all our arms.”\n–Webber\n“Ten more, please!”\n–Walani\n“More like \"umami\"! Ooooh, mommy!”\n–Warly\n“Eat a eel? It be breakfast already?”\n–Woodlegs\n“WILBA LIKETH CAVE ROT AND WATER SNAKE”\n–Wilba\n“Sea Wiggly for belly”\n–Wormwood\n“Wrap it anyway you like, it's still a dead fish.”\n–Wheeler\n“Fancy eats.”\n–Winona\n“Yet another dish cooked up by mortals.”\n–Wortox\n“That not what you do with fish, flort!”\n–Wurt\n“Bite-sized deliciousness.”\n–Walter\n“It makes the eel slightly better.”\n–Wanda\nUnagi is a Meat Food item cooked in the Crock Pot by adding 1 Eel and 1 Lichen. It takes 10 seconds to cook.\nUnagi has the highest Crock Pot Priority (20) in the Don't Starve base game. This means that placing an Eel and Lichen into any recipe will always result in Unagi.\nIt restores less Hunger than the Eel and Lichen combined, but heals 20 and 5 , so it can be useful whenever player's health is low. However, it spoils in 10 days (which is also affected by the Lichen's fast spoil time), so it is recommended to only cook it when needed or put it in an Ice Box.\nPrerequisites[edit | edit source]\nRequires:\nRequire\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×2\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\nA recipe for Unagi that provides as much hunger value as possible.\n×3\n×2\n×2\nAn example of Unagi's priority.\n×2\n×2\n50% chance to result in Ceviche\nTips[edit | edit source]\nIf the player has easy access to Monster Meat, making a Surf 'n' Turf can be a better alternative than the Unagi.\nSince Unagi has no filler restrictions, it can be used to regain Health and Sanity quickly in the Ruins by using either the naturally spawning Blue Caps or dropped Monster Meat as filler.\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nUnagi in Japanese means eel.\nThe Unagi as shown in the game depicts an Unakyu, which is eel used to prepare sushi.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nIcon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord",
