  "title": "Unagi",
  "wikitext": "{{Navbutton/Separation}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = Unagi.png\n|image = Unagi Dropped.png\n|canBeBurned=1\n|foodType = [[Food Type#Meat|Meat]] {{Pic|32px|Meats|Food Type#Meat}}\n|foodRecipe = {{Pic|32px|Eel}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Lichen}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x2\n|hpRestored = 20\n|hungerRestored = 18.75\n|sanityRestored = 5\n|cooktime = 10 sec\n|spoil = 10 days\n|stack = 40\n|spawnCode = \"unagi\"\n|priority = 20\n|crafting = Cooked in a [[Crock Pot]]}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = I hope this doesn't make me feel eel!\n|willow = You can make it fancy but it's still an eel.\n|wolfgang = Food makes me mighty!\n|wendy = It looks more appetizing this way.\n|wx78 = A FANCIER FUEL PACK.\n|wickerbottom = A common way to prepare eel.\n|woodie = It'll fill ya up.\n|maxwell = It will have to do.\n|wagstaff = I do hope this doesn't cause stomach upset.\n|wigfrid = Nö need för fööd tö be sö fancy.\n|webber = It was easy to make with all our arms.\n|walani = Ten more, please!\n|warly = More like \"umami\"! Ooooh, mommy!\n|woodlegs = Eat a eel? It be breakfast already?\n|wilba = WILBA LIKETH CAVE ROT AND WATER SNAKE\n|wormwood = Sea Wiggly for belly\n|wheeler = Wrap it anyway you like, it's still a dead fish.\n|winona = Fancy eats.\n|wortox = Yet another dish cooked up by mortals.\n|wurt = That not what you do with fish, flort!\n|walter = Bite-sized deliciousness.\n|wanda = It makes the eel slightly better.\n|choose = willow}}\n'''Unagi''' is a [[Meats|Meat]] [[Food]] [[item]] cooked in the [[Crock Pot]] by adding 1 [[Eel]] and 1 [[Lichen]]. It takes 10 seconds to cook.\n\nUnagi has the highest [[Crock Pot#Priority|Crock Pot Priority]] (20) in the ''[[Don't Starve]]'' base game. This means that placing an Eel and Lichen into any recipe will always result in Unagi.\n\nIt restores less [[Hunger]] than the Eel and Lichen combined, but heals 20 {{Hp}} and 5 {{Sanity}}, so it can be useful whenever player's health is low. However, it [[spoil]]s in 10 days (which is also affected by the Lichen's fast spoil time), so it is recommended to only cook it when needed or put it in an [[Ice Box]].\n\n== Prerequisites ==\n* Requires: [[File:Eels.png|link=Eel]]\n* Require [[File:Lichen.png|link=Lichen]]\n\n=={{pic|32|Cookbook}} Recipe==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eels\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Filler\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi}}\n\n==Examples==\n{{Recipe\n|item = Eel\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Twigs\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi|note={{Pic24|Prototype}} A recipe for Unagi that provides as much hunger value as possible.}}\n{{Recipe\n|item = Eel\n|item2 = Lichen\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi|count2=3}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eels\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Monster Meat\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eels\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Mushrooms\n|item4 = Monster Meats \n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eels\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Mandrake\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi\n|note = An example of Unagi's priority.}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eels\n|item2 = Lichen\n|item3 = Ice\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Unagi\n|dlc = Reign of Giants}}\n{{Recipe|item1 = eels|item2 = lichen|item4 = ice|dlc =SW|tool = Crock Pot|result = Unagi|note = 50% chance to result in [[Ceviche]] |count1=2}}\n\n== {{Pic32|Prototype}} Tips ==\n* If the player has easy access to [[Monster Meat]], making a [[Surf 'n' Turf]] can be a better alternative than the Unagi.\n*Since Unagi has no filler restrictions, it can be used to regain Health and Sanity quickly in the [[Ruins]] by using either the naturally spawning [[Mushrooms#Blue Mushroom|Blue Caps]] or dropped Monster Meat as filler.\n\n=={{pic|32|Placeholder}} Trivia==\n*[[Wikipedia:Unagi|Unagi]] in Japanese means ''eel''.\n**The Unagi as shown in the game depicts an ''Unakyu'', which is eel used to prepare sushi.\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nUnagi 128x128.png|Icon used as emoji for Official Klei Discord\n</gallery>\n__NOTOC__\n[[vi:Unagi]]\n[[fr:Unagis]]\n[[Category:Flammable Objects]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Sanity Boost]]"
}
